<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-16T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="770" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.5914/26</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Minister <persName type="to">Egan</persName>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-16T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 16, 1915, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>27. Department is of the opinion that plan suggested in your despatch
                                No. 833, March 8, is desirable and may be feasible and you may very
                                discreetly approach the proper officials with a view to ascertaining
                                whether a proposal such as contemplated would be received not
                                unfavorably.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>